James de Villiers, News24(iStock) (iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Grahamstown &ndash; Ten people are in a critical condition after a bus carrying 59 church-goers overturned on the R67 between Fort Beaufort and Grahamstown on Saturday, authorities said.&nbsp;The ten people were taken to the Livingston hospital in Port Elizabeth, Eastern Cape Health spokesperson Sizwe Kupelo said.&nbsp;Injures include fractured ribs, pelvis and spines.&nbsp;No casualties were reported. Additional information surrounding the incident was not immediately available.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.